Q6
'Hello, world!'[1] == 'e'
'Hello, world!'[0:5] == 'Hello'
'Hello, world!'[:5] == 'Hello'
'Hello, world!'[3:] == 'lo, world!'
_____________________________________________________________________________

Q7
'Hello'.upper() == 'HELLO'
'Hello'.upper().isupper() == 'True'
'Hello'.upper().lower() == 'hello'
_____________________________________________________________________________

Q8
'Remember, remember, the fifth of July.'.split() == ['Remember,', 'remember,', 'the', 'fifth', 'of', 'July.']
'-'.join('There can only one'.split()) == 'There-can-only-one'
__________________________________________________________________________

Q9
str.ljust(len , fillchar) -----> left alignment of a string with  len of string and fillchar with charcaters to fill in whitespaces
str.rjust( len , fillchar) -----> right alignment of a string with  len of string and fillchar with charcaters to fill in whitespaces
str.center(len , fillchar) -----> center alignment of a string with  len of string and fillchar with charcaters to fill in whitespaces
_______________________________________________________________________________

